Tammy Petersen, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - A family of four was killed in a shack fire in Bloekombos early on Sunday morning, City of Cape Town fire services said.Firefighters arrived at 05:30 where two fire engines, one rescue vehicle and a tanker tackled the blaze, spokesperson Theo Layne said. The bodies of two adults and their children were found.&ldquo;It is suspected that a heating device may have been the cause, however this remains undetermined,&rdquo; Layne said.The matter was handed to police for further investigation.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.